news.headline: Banks’ Wealth Management Units Ride Market Rebound in Second Quarter
news.summary: Assets under management at some of the nation’s largest wealth management businesses are up, but net new assets for the second quarter tell a more nuanced story.

news.headline: Citi hires senior JPMorgan bankers to strengthen financing business
news.summary: Aloke Gupte, previously co-head of international equity capital markets (ECM) at JPMorgan, will join Citi as global co-head of ECM alongside Doug Adams.  Alex Watkins, who held the same role as Gupte at JPMorgan, will take over as head of technology financing.
